main event: Multiple UFO sightings reported over the West End area of New Jersey on September 9, 1952.
interesting points: There were multiple sightings over a 2-hour period, with up to 10 objects observed at one time.
The objects were described as reddish-orange in color, flashing at a rate of 2-3 flashes per second.
The objects moved horizontally with no change in elevation and made no sound.
The sightings were reported by numerous reliable sources, including a flight of four UFO objects.
The report mentions that a McGuire Air Force officer stated that some of the objects seemed to be above the water.
